AND FURTHER AMEND by inserting the following new section immediately preceding the last
section and renumbering the subsequent section accordingly:
SECTION 4. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 8-8-201, is amended by adding the
following new subsection:
(c) A sheriff, jail administrator, or deputy jailer whose duty it is to receive persons
arrested pursuant to law may refuse or delay acceptance of an arrestee as provided in §
41-4-145.
